<h1 id="using-coffeescript-in-a-sails-app">Using CoffeeScript in a Sails App</h1>
<p>Sails supports using CoffeeScript to write your custom app code (like <a href="http://www.sailsjs.com/documentation/concepts/actions-and-controllers">actions</a> and <a href="http://www.sailsjs.com/documentation/concepts/core-concepts-table-of-contents/models-and-orm">models</a>).  You can enable this support in three steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>Run <code>npm install coffee-script</code> in your app folder.</li>
<li>Add the following line at the top of your app&apos;s <code>app.js</code> file:<pre><code class="javascript">require(&apos;coffee-script/register&apos;);
</code></pre><!-- __LANG=%%__ --></li>
<li>Start your app with <code>node app.js</code> instead of <code>sails lift</code>.</li>
</ol>
